{
  "stem": "3360.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And they saw someone who would pass them up and not give them money, they would immediately know who that was because they were people from the various neighborhoods.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Then you heard Hitler's, Hitler's voice blasting by loudspeaker at least once a week on the streets.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "All of-- all of those kinds of things, that's how, you know, things went on after they took over the government.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Almost immediately, they started flying airplanes.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So within, within a few months, you know, they planned on making war later-- within a few months.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The SA was-- those were really the lower-- the lower-class Nazis that actually stood-- it stood for 'Sturmabteilung,' as far as I, I can remember.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Whereas the SS stood for [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] 'Schutzstaffel,' the elite guard.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, '33 through '39, during their regime.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I'm from 9, 9 through 15.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, at first, a lot of Jews, and even a lot of Germans, who had seen this thing come about, of them being empowered, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] thought it couldn't last, that it was just too ridiculous to last, that their plans were outrageous that the former, you know, so-called allies-- or like France, France and England, would never stand for it.",
      "word_count": 63
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But as it was, they were sick and tired of having fought the First World War.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they were still feeling the terrible effects of that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That it would not last?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--my father thought maybe it might not last.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My mother thought it would last and get worse.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My mother, always, from the very beginning, had that feeling, and correctly so.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she started pushing my father to write-- my father had three sisters in the United States.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
